# {{ code }} — Learning Objectives

## Objective

> {{ objectiveText }}

**Bloom's Taxonomy Level**: {{ bloomsLevel }}

## Bloom's Taxonomy Context

{% if bloomsLevel == "Remember" %}
**Level 1 - Remember**: Recall facts and basic concepts. Focuses on knowledge retention and identification of key terms and definitions.
{% elif bloomsLevel == "Understand" %}
**Level 2 - Understand**: Explain ideas or concepts. Focuses on comprehension, interpretation, and discussion.
{% elif bloomsLevel == "Apply" %}
**Level 3 - Apply**: Use information in new situations. Focuses on practical application to real-world problems.
{% elif bloomsLevel == "Analyze" %}
**Level 4 - Analyze**: Draw connections among ideas. Focuses on breaking down complex problems and identifying relationships.
{% elif bloomsLevel == "Evaluate" %}
**Level 5 - Evaluate**: Justify a stand or decision. Focuses on critical assessment, judgment, and validation.
{% elif bloomsLevel == "Create" %}
**Level 6 - Create**: Produce new or original work. Focuses on synthesis, design, and novel solution development.
{% endif %}

## Assessment Method

{% if bloomsLevel == "Remember" or bloomsLevel == "Understand" %}
- Knowledge check quiz
- Written explanation of concepts
{% elif bloomsLevel == "Apply" %}
- Hands-on exercise with tools
- Case study application
{% elif bloomsLevel == "Analyze" %}
- Data analysis exercise
- Root cause analysis
{% elif bloomsLevel == "Evaluate" %}
- Critical review of results
- Peer evaluation exercise
{% else %}
- Design project deliverable
- Capstone project component
{% endif %}

